00:04:29.556 --> 00:04:36.736 A:middle
If users don't respond to an ad,
we'll stop showing it to them.

00:04:37.526 --> 00:04:39.776 A:middle
Pricing is a Cost Per Tap model.

00:04:39.856 --> 00:04:42.646 A:middle
So you only pay when a
user engages with your ad,

00:04:42.956 --> 00:04:45.256 A:middle
and you decide the maximum
amount you're willing

00:04:45.256 --> 00:04:46.046 A:middle
to pay for a tap.

00:04:47.406 --> 00:04:51.036 A:middle
The actual cost of
that tap is a result

00:04:51.036 --> 00:04:52.406 A:middle
of a Second Price Auction,

00:04:52.406 --> 00:04:54.646 A:middle
meaning the price
you pay is based

00:04:54.646 --> 00:04:57.096 A:middle
on what your nearest
competitor is willing to pay

00:04:57.096 --> 00:04:59.776 A:middle
to show their ad up
to your maximum bid.

00:05:00.616 --> 00:05:02.956 A:middle
This means you'll never pay more
than you're willing to spend

00:05:03.456 --> 00:05:06.466 A:middle
or more than you need to.

00:05:07.576 --> 00:05:10.766 A:middle
